# Edge case: pre-formed RING complex declared in seed species
# Tests:  ListOfSpecies bond resolution must handle a complete ring
#         (every molecule connected to two others through TWO bonds).
#         A 3-cycle in seed species is the simplest case where the
#         bond-pair resolver has no "loose end" to start from.  RM's
#         load_model resolves bonds via XML id pairs
#         (simulator.cpp:638-657); if the pair-resolution traversal
#         relies on a particular tree shape, it would either drop a
#         bond or mis-orient one.  We add a state-transition rule
#         that DOES fire so the network is non-trivial and ODE
#         reference is meaningful: each A in the ring carries a
#         flippable spin, and one rule cycles spins regardless of
#         topology.  The strict-`+` break rule remains as a probe of
#         the same-complex check (it must REFUSE to fire on any A
#         in a ring because both bond endpoints stay connected).
# Edge:   we mix pre-formed 3-cycles with free monomers so the
#         simulator sees both ring and chain topologies live.  Spin
#         transitions must reach the rings AND the monomers; bond
#         break must work only on the (currently absent) free dimer
#         population.  In ODE, the spin variable splits the species
#         population into 2^N within-ring conformers — keeps the
#         network finite and small (HNauty canonicalisation dedup).
# Tier:   base

begin model
setOption("SpeciesLabel","HNauty")
begin parameters
    A_ring   3      # pre-formed 3-cycles (= 9 bonded molecules)
    A_mono   12     # free monomer A's
    k_flip   0.20   # /s, spin-flip rate (uniform up<->dn)
    kr_break 0.5
end parameters

begin molecule types
    A(l,r,sp~up~dn)
end molecule types

begin seed species
    # Triangle ring with all spins down — the canonical loose-end-free seed.
    A(l!1,r!2,sp~dn).A(l!2,r!3,sp~dn).A(l!3,r!1,sp~dn)   A_ring
    # Free monomers as a baseline population.
    A(l,r,sp~dn)                                          A_mono
end seed species

begin observables
    Molecules  A_total      A()
    Molecules  A_up         A(sp~up)
    Molecules  A_dn         A(sp~dn)
    Molecules  A_free_l     A(l)
    Molecules  A_bound_l    A(l!+)
    Species    Mono         A(l,r)
end observables

begin reaction rules
    # Spin transitions — fire on every A regardless of bonds.
    A(sp~dn) <-> A(sp~up)   k_flip, k_flip
    # Strict-`+` break — REFUSES on the closed ring (bond break
    # leaves all 3 molecules connected via the other two bonds).
    # In the seed there are zero free dimers so this never fires
    # but RM's generation/observation paths must not break.
    A(l,r!1).A(l!1,r) -> A(l,r) + A(l,r)   kr_break
end reaction rules
end model

begin actions
simulate({method=>"nf",t_end=>20,n_steps=>40,param=>"-bscb"})
end actions
